    [5]:
    df_mod = df
    # Convert 'datetime' to useful numeric features
    df_mod['datetime'] = pd.to_datetime(df_mod['datetime'], errors='coerce')
    df_mod['year'] = df_mod['datetime'].dt.year
    df_mod['month'] = df_mod['datetime'].dt.month

    df_mod['day'] = df_mod['datetime'].dt.day

    # Encode 'Wildfire' as 0/1
    df_mod['Wildfire'] = df_mod['Wildfire'].astype(str).str.lower()
    df_mod['Wildfire'] = df_mod['Wildfire'].map({'yes': 1, 'no': 0})

    # Drop the original 'datetime' column
    df_mod = df_mod.drop(columns=['datetime'])

    # Select only numeric columns
    numeric_cols = []

    for col in df_mod.columns:
    if df_mod[col].dtype in ['int64', 'float64','int32']:
    numeric_cols.append(col)

    print(numeric_cols)

    # Compute correlation matrix
    corr_matrix = df_mod[numeric_cols].corr()

    import folium
    from folium.plugins import HeatMap

    # Filter only wildfire points
    wildfire_df = df_mod[df_mod['Wildfire'] == 1].copy()

    # Prepare data as list of [lat, lon]
    heat_data = list(zip(wildfire_df['latitude'], wildfire_df['longitude']))

    # Create base map centered on USA
    m = folium.Map(
    location=[37.8, -96],
    zoom_start=4,
    tiles='CartoDB dark_matter',
    zoom_control=False,
    scrollWheelZoom=False,
    dragging=False,
    touchZoom=False
    )
    gradient = { 0.0: '#0000ff', # blau per intensitats baixes
    0.3: '#00ffff', # cian
    0.5: '#ffff00', # groc
    0.7: '#ff8000', # taronja
    1.0: '#ff0000' # vermell intens
    }


    # Add heatmap layer
    HeatMap(
    heat_data,
    radius=4,
    blur=6,
    max_zoom=13,
    gradient=gradient
    ).add_to(m)

    monthly_data = df_mod.groupby('month').agg({
    'pr': 'mean',
    'Wildfire': 'sum'
    }).reset_index()
    [21]:
    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,6))

    # Bar plot: average rainfall
    bar1 = ax1.bar(monthly_data['month'], monthly_data['pr'], color='skyblue', alpha=0.6, label='Avg Rainfall (pr)')
    ax1.set_ylabel('Average Rainfall (pr)', color='blue')
    ax1.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax1.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor='blue')

    # Line plot: wildfire counts
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()
    line1,=ax2.plot(monthly_data['month'], monthly_data['Wildfire'], color='red', marker='o', label='Wildfire Count')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Number of Wildfires', color='red')
    ax2.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor='red')

    plt.title('Effect of Monthly Rainfall on Wildfires')
    lines_labels = [bar1, line1]
    labels = [l.get_label() for l in lines_labels]
    ax1.legend(lines_labels, labels, loc='upper right')
    fig.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # Select the features you mentioned
    features = ['pr', 'rmax', 'rmin', 'sph', 'srad', 'tmmn', 'tmmx', 'vs', 'vpd',
    'fm100', 'fm1000', 'erc', 'bi', 'etr', 'pet']

    # Calculate mean of each feature
    means = df_mod[features].mean()

    # Normalize to percentages
    percentages = 100 * means / means.sum()

    # Pie chart labels (you can customize them)
    labels = ['Precipitation', 'Rel Humidity Max', 'Rel Humidity Min', 'Specific Humidity',
    'Solar Radiation', 'Temp Min', 'Temp Max', 'Wind Speed', 'Vapor Pressure Deficit',
    'Fuel Moisture 100hr', 'Fuel Moisture 1000hr', 'Energy Release Comp',
    'Burning Index', 'Evapotranspiration (etr)', 'Potential ET (pet)']

    # Plot pie chart
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,12))
    plt.pie(percentages, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=140)
    plt.title('Relative Contribution of Features (Mean Values Normalized)')
    plt.axis('equal') # Equal aspect ratio ensures pie is circular.
    plt.show()

    import geopandas as gpd
    import pandas as pd
    from shapely.geometry import Point
    import folium
    url_states = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/python-visualization/folium/master/examples/data/us-states.json'

    # Convertir el teu df a GeoDataFrame
    gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame(
    df_mod,
    geometry=gpd.points_from_xy(df.longitude, df.latitude),
    crs="EPSG:4326"
    )

    # Carregar estats USA
    states = gpd.read_file(url_states)

    # Unir punts amb estats
    gdf = gpd.sjoin(gdf, states, how="left", predicate="within")

    # La columna amb el nom de l’estat sol ser 'name'

    fires_by_state = gdf.groupby('name').size().reset_index(name='count')

    m = folium.Map(location=[37.8, -96], zoom_start=4, tiles='CartoDB positron')

    folium.Choropleth(
    geo_data=url_states,
    name='choropleth',
    data=fires_by_state,
    columns=['name', 'count'],
    key_on='feature.properties.name',
    fill_color='YlOrRd',
    fill_opacity=0.8,
    line_opacity=0.3,
    legend_name='Nombre d’incendis per estat'
    ).add_to(m)

    m
